      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation metric E/uval < 1.96 and QoI difference < 10% for all three quantities of interest.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness: E/uval = 0.83, difference 3.1%. Yield force: E/uval = 1.14, difference 4.7%. Force at 40 mm: E/uval = 1.31, difference 6.2%. All three QoIs satisfy both acceptance criteria. Validation metric computed per ASME V&V 40 Section 5.3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly linked to the regulatory submission requirements and clinical failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield force are primary regulatory endpoints per FDA guidance on spinal implant testing. Force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield behavior relevant to fatigue life prediction. All three QoIs directly support the 510(k) submission claim."
