    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-level factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) reflects the single-condition nature of ASTM F1717 and is accepted because F1717 is the applicable regulatory standard and no additional loading conditions are within the COU scope. Validation metric E/uval < 1.96 and QoI differences < 10% satisfied for all three quantities of interest across N=11 constructs from two independent laboratories. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the regulatory submission claim.",
